---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout>
  <nav>
    <a href="#top" class="nav-wordmark">Noema<span class="period">.</span></a>
    <a
      href="https://github.com/Fail-Safe/Noema"
      class="github-link"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >GitHub ↗</a>
  </nav>

  <main id="top">
    <section class="hero">
      <img src="/brand/noema-dark.svg" alt="Noema." width="2314" height="522" />
      <p class="tagline">The intentional memory layer for your AI agents.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/Fail-Safe/Noema"
          class="cta"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >View on GitHub</a>
        <a href="#install" class="cta-text">Get started ↓</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="content">
      <section class="prose">
        <p>
          Noema gives AI agents — and the humans working alongside them — a persistent, structured
          place to record what they know, decide, observe, and intend. Every memory is a plain
          markdown file. The index is a local SQLite database. Nothing lives in the cloud; nothing
          requires an API key.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="prose">
        <h2>Why Noema?</h2>
        <ul class="why-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Local-first.</strong>
            No cloud, no API keys, no account required. Your memories live in <code>~/.noema/</code>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Plain markdown.</strong>
            Every Trace is a file. You can <code>cat</code>, <code>grep</code>, and <code>git commit</code> it — no proprietary format.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>MCP-native.</strong>
            Works with Claude Code, Copilot, Zed, and any MCP-compatible agent out of the box.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="prose">
        <h2>Concepts</h2>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Term</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Trace</td>
              <td>A single memory — one markdown file + its database row</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Cortex</td>
              <td>A named collection of Traces, stored in a directory you control</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>
          Every Trace has a type that describes its intent —
          <code>fact</code>, <code>decision</code>, <code>preference</code>,
          <code>context</code>, <code>skill</code>, <code>intent</code>,
          <code>observation</code>, or <code>note</code>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="prose" id="install">
        <h2>Get started</h2>
        <p>Requires Go 1.21+.</p>
        <pre><code><span class="prompt">$ </span>go install github.com/Fail-Safe/Noema/cmd/noema@latest
<span class="prompt">$ </span>noema init --name my-cortex
<span class="prompt">$ </span>noema serve --transport stdio</code></pre>
        <p>
          For full setup, federation, and MCP configuration see the
          <a href="https://github.com/Fail-Safe/Noema" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">README</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <a href="https://github.com/Fail-Safe/Noema" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
    &nbsp;·&nbsp; MIT License
    &nbsp;·&nbsp; <a href="mailto:contact@noemacortex.com">contact@noemacortex.com</a>
  </footer>
</Layout>
